{"id":32780,"date":"2019-07-13T13:30:16","date_gmt":"2019-07-13T09:30:16","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=32780"},"modified":"2025-03-01T19:50:55","modified_gmt":"2025-03-01T15:50:55","slug":"umar-riddah-murtad-silm","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/13\/umar-riddah-murtad-silm\/","title":{"rendered":"Umar on Apostasy: Apostates return peacefully or imprisoned"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Anas ibn Malik reported: I said, \u201cO commander of the faithful, some people have turned renegade against Islam and joined the idolaters. What is to be done other than killing them?\u201d Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThat I take hold of them on peaceful terms is more beloved to me than everything over which the sun rises, from the horizon to the zenith.\u201d I said, \u201cO commander of the faithful, what would you do if you seized them?\u201d Umar said, \u201cI would offer them the door through which they exited, that they would enter it again. If they did so, I would accept it from them; otherwise, I would keep them in prison.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Ibrahim al-Nakha&#8217;i said about the apostate, &#8220;He is held for his repentance indefinitely,&#8221; and Sufyan al-Thawri said, &#8220;This is what we adhere to.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: Mus\u0323annaf &#8216;Abd al-Razza\u0304q 18696<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Ibn Kathir<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0645\u0650\u064a\u0631\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0624\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0646\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u064c \u0627\u0631\u0652\u062a\u064e\u062f\u0651\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0625\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650 \u0